UML:TaggedValue.value: <memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall recieve detailed digital map before the start of journey.
<memo>#NOTES#Global map shall be used to roughly plan a path from start to destination.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall combine the inputs from different sensors to produce the required information.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall avoid colliding with the potenial obstacles.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall stabilize the platform as the trajectory is followed.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall follow the generated trajectory.

<memo>#NOTES#It requires that the vehicle shall set the values of actuators for it to autonomously follow the derived trajectory and perform additional stabilization maneuvers to ensure that it stays on the defined track.
<memo>#NOTES#The Vehicle shall autonomously travel from start point to the destination.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall generate an executable trajectory.
<memo>#NOTES#Local map shall be used for precise trajectory generation
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall manage trajectory generation depending on the inputs recieved.
<memo>#NOTES#For the vehicle to be able to drive by itself to a user defined destination, it is required to receive the destination and a digital map as inputs, before the start of journey.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall sense its internal state and external environment.

<memo>#NOTES#To ensure that the input map is available to the vehicle in a perceivable format and the input destination is added in relation to the given map, Map Server is required for processing the raw input data.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall locate its position on given map.

<memo>#NOTES#Since it is expected by the vehicle to autonomously navigate its way to destination, it shall understand the external environment, its internal state and its location with reference to the given map.

<memo>#NOTES#To achieve autonomous driving functionality of the vehicle, it shall plan its way towards the goal by generating a virtual trajectory for the vehicle to follow. Additionally, to ensure that the obstacles are efficiently avoided from potential collisions, when encountered, the generated trajectory shall be managed according to the type of obstacle.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall travel in the shortest possible time.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall recieve the input for final destination before the start of journey.
<memo>#NOTES#The vehicle shall generatecollision free trajectory toward its destination.
